In this statement, President Barack Obama addresses the participants of the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT) Review Conference. He emphasizes the importance of upholding the rights and responsibilities of all nations in order to prevent the spread of nuclear weapons. Obama states that the NPT has been the cornerstone of efforts to prevent the proliferation of nuclear weapons for four decades, but it is currently under increasing pressure. He highlights the United States' commitment to strengthening the NPT and working towards nuclear disarmament. Obama also urges nations without nuclear weapons to forsake them, as history has shown that this path leads to greater security and opportunity. He emphasizes the importance of nations abiding by their obligations and accessing peaceful nuclear energy. Obama concludes by calling on nations to meet their responsibilities and pursue a world without nuclear weapons.